    <!-- First run -->
    <string name="how_to_title">Help</string>
    <string name="first_run_title">Welcome to %s</string> <!-- '%s' is the App name (name="app_name") -->
    <string name="first_run_message">Chronus is a Widget and needs to be manually added to either the Home screen (Android 4.1+) or the
        Lock screen (only possible on Android 4.2+) using the widget picker feature of Android and your launcher.\n\nOnce the widget is
        placed, you can use this app to change the widget configuration.\n\nRemember to resize the widget on your screen to make space for all the
        panels you have enabled (Clock, Weather and Calendar) since the widget will automatically hide panels if its not big enough.\n\nFor
        the best results, I recommended using either the Apex or Nova launchers. Chronus will work on most launchers but the ability to configure how
        it is displayed may be limited.\n\nFor Android 4.2+, to add a widget to the Lock screen, slide left on the Lock screen and then use
        the add widget button (+) to add Chronus. Lock screen widgets can be rearranged by long-pressing then moving or deleting them.</string>

    <string name="no_widget_message">At least one Chronus Widget must be added to either the Home or the
        Lock screen before you can use this app to change its configuration.\n\nWidgets can be added using the widget
        picker feature of Android and your launcher.</string>

